{
  "texts": [
    "Simultaneous relaxation of the two groups leads to substantial improvement, in particular an amide group very close to reference structural values.",
    "Such errors in the heteroatom skeleton propagate further when assigning and counting hydrogen atoms.",
    "In the 5GTR structure 37, a guanidino group strongly deviates from the expected planarity.",
    "The immediate consequences are incorrect atomic hybridizations and overassignment of hydrogen atoms, with a local formal charge of +3 in a radius of one bond around the central carbon.",
    "More examples are described in Supplementary Information."
  ]
}